Cell[TextData[{
 "Otra vez vemos que ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|
    "boxes" -> FormBox["\[Alpha]", TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "\\alpha", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "702845a5-de3a-e74a-89ae-3b95b4ccf4d6"],
 " es la probabilidad de convencimiento m\[AAcute]xima y ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       StyleBox["A", "TI"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "A", 
     "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6a1c88a7-f8ab-9f4e-b8e9-c899d26825d5"],
 " es el n\[UAcute]mero de personas necesarias en el movimiento para que la \
probabilidad de convencimiento sea m\[AAcute]xima. Mientras m\[AAcute]s chico \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       StyleBox["A", "TI"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "A", 
     "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1150c151-d288-4b49-bb86-2fac861a1bc0"],
 ", menos personas son necesarias para tener una gran probabilidad de \
convencimiento, y vice versa.\nDado que esta es una funci\[OAcute]n definida \
a trozos, el an\[AAcute]lisis tambi\[EAcute]n debe hacerse a trozos.\n\
Empezamos por el caso m\[AAcute]s f\[AAcute]cil, si ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         StyleBox["N", "TI"], ">", 
         StyleBox["A", "TI"]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "N>A", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2ec6f524-5839-f54e-acca-518e269f5d22"],
 ", entonces ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         StyleBox["c", "TI"], 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           StyleBox["N", "TI"], ")"}], "\[LongEqual]", "\[Alpha]"}], 
       TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "c(N)=\\alpha", "state" -> 
     "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a49e9822-608a-c145-b53e-2584dc564c6a"],
 " y tenemos que \n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         StyleBox["f", "TI"], 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           StyleBox["N", "TI"], ")"}], "\[LongEqual]", "\[Alpha]", 
         StyleBox["N", "TI"], 
         FractionBox[
          RowBox[{
            StyleBox["P", "TI"], "-", 
            StyleBox["N", "TI"]}], 
          StyleBox["P", "TI"]], "-", "\[Mu]", 
         StyleBox["N", "TI"]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "f(N)=\\alpha N\\frac{P-N}{P}-\\mu N", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "50083516-b61f-6344-84c5-4d83dfc22591"],
 "\nAl calcular los puntos de equilibrio, vemos de inmediato que ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         StyleBox["N", "TI"], "\[LongEqual]", "0"}], TraditionalForm], 
     "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "N=0", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5882ae26-dd7c-a44f-ac86-c347f5c8762c"],
 " es una soluci\[OAcute]n de equilibrio. Sin embargo, este caso no es \
realista, pues necesitamos que ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         StyleBox["N", "TI"], ">", 
         StyleBox["A", "TI"]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "N>A", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "40286db9-a703-ac47-9496-4bee198c0032"],
 " y como ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       StyleBox["A", "TI"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "A", 
     "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cf03d219-4eb1-454e-9ad1-915d39bbfab2"],
 " es un n\[UAcute]mero positivo de personas, tenemos que ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{"0", "<", 
         StyleBox["A", "TI"]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "0<A", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c3a065a3-0195-9447-ae8b-8f03f1f28ad4"],
 ", por lo que no caemos en este caso. Eliminando esta posibilidad, \
necesitamos que \n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", 
         StyleBox["P", "TI"], "-", "\[Alpha]", 
         SuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["N", "TI"], "*"], "-", "\[Mu]", 
         StyleBox["P", "TI"], "\[LongEqual]", "0"}], TraditionalForm], 
     "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "\\alpha P-\\alpha N^*-\\mu P=0", "state" -> 
     "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c3dbc298-64e7-1145-9c0a-36a4007dd240"],
 ",\npor lo que la soluci\[OAcute]n de equilibrio es ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["N", "TI"], "*"], "\[LongEqual]", 
         FractionBox[
          RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", "-", "\[Mu]"}], "\[Alpha]"], 
         StyleBox["P", "TI"]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "N^*=\\frac{\\alpha-\\mu}{\\alpha}P", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e6780ad5-74bc-cf4b-b6d6-a5c4ae445828"],
 ". Vemos que esta soluci\[OAcute]n de equilibrio s\[OAcute]lo es realista si \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", ">", "\[Mu]"}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, 
     "input" -> "\\alpha>\\mu", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6ed5dc0f-46e3-b043-9d3a-230705bd2515"],
 ", de otro modo es negativa y no representa una poblaci\[OAcute]n real. \
Calculando su estabilidad tenemos que \n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["f", "TI"], "\[Prime]"], 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           StyleBox["N", "TI"], ")"}], "\[LongEqual]", 
         FractionBox["\[Alpha]", 
          StyleBox["P", "TI"]], 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           RowBox[{
             StyleBox["P", "TI"], "-", "2", 
             StyleBox["N", "TI"]}], ")"}], "-", "\[Mu]"}], TraditionalForm], 
     "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "f'(N)=\\frac{\\alpha}{P}(P-2N)-\\mu", 
     "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7c8eb126-754a-8f4d-a3a9-39f1ac49d5b8"],
 ".\nEvaluando ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       SuperscriptBox[
        StyleBox["N", "TI"], "*"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "N^*", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2a9dea92-56f3-f543-b07c-bd0efc6012ba"],
 ", tenemos \n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         StyleBox["f", "TI"], 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           SuperscriptBox[
            StyleBox["N", "TI"], "*"], ")"}], "\[LongEqual]", "\[Mu]", "-", 
         "\[Alpha]"}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "f(N^*)=\\mu-\\alpha", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "baacbd81-be7d-a64a-a813-529a9bcc4d39"],
 ".\nPero dijimos que para que esta soluci\[OAcute]n fuera realista, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", ">", "\[Mu]"}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, 
     "input" -> "\\alpha>\\mu", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "dbe621bd-3311-8044-9965-8ac3ea1f4b43"],
 ", por lo que ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{"\[Mu]", "-", "\[Alpha]", "<", "0"}], TraditionalForm], 
     "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "\\mu-\\alpha<0", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "665400e3-22d0-634e-993d-92f29572ed66"],
 ", y siempre es estable. Por lo tanto nunca hay bifurcaci\[OAcute]n en este \
caso. Pero podemos concluir que, si ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         StyleBox["N", "TI"], ">", 
         StyleBox["A", "TI"]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "N>A", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "be167ea7-d51f-6a4f-96e5-6466fb497978"],
 " (si hay m\[AAcute]s personas en el movimiento que la cantidad necesaria \
para tener un convencimiento m\[AAcute]ximo) y si ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", ">", "\[Mu]"}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, 
     "input" -> "\\alpha>\\mu", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "583c1b07-e28b-c646-a123-337fa147fd8a"],
 ", es decir que la probabilidad de convencimiento es mayor a la probabilidad \
de olvido, entonces el movimiento podr\[IAcute]a sobrevivir, con un \
n\[UAcute]mero ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         FractionBox[
          RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", "-", "\[Mu]"}], "\[Alpha]"], 
         StyleBox["P", "TI"]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "\\frac{\\alpha-\\mu}{\\alpha}P", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4f0fcef9-1c2d-5843-afa9-144033076112"],
 " en el movimiento despu\[EAcute]s de mucho tiempo.\nAhora consideramos el \
caso ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         StyleBox["N", "TI"], "<", 
         StyleBox["A", "TI"]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "N<A", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fa2ad005-9419-e94b-b6a3-da1d2c2f79f0"],
 ". En este caso ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         StyleBox["c", "TI"], 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           StyleBox["N", "TI"], ")"}], "\[LongEqual]", "\[Alpha]", 
         FractionBox[
          StyleBox["N", "TI"], 
          StyleBox["A", "TI"]]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "c(N)=\\alpha\\frac{N}{A}", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "df73986f-0a0b-8f4d-9e06-5341edd7cf4d"],
 " y tenemos que\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         StyleBox["f", "TI"], 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           StyleBox["N", "TI"], ")"}], "\[LongEqual]", 
         FractionBox[
          RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", 
            StyleBox["N", "TI"]}], 
          StyleBox["A", "TI"]], 
         StyleBox["N", "TI"], 
         FractionBox[
          RowBox[{
            StyleBox["P", "TI"], "-", 
            StyleBox["N", "TI"]}], 
          StyleBox["P", "TI"]], "-", "\[Mu]", 
         StyleBox["N", "TI"]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "f(N)=\\frac{\\alpha N}{A}N\\frac{P-N}{P}-\\mu N", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9416058c-c971-964f-aa0d-c8d08a11e063"],
 "\nNaturalmente, un punto de equilibrio es ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SubsuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["N", "TI"], "1", "*"], "\[LongEqual]", "0"}], 
       TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "N_1^*=0", "state" -> 
     "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9830a601-f6de-694b-aec5-5c7ddf59ebba"],
 ", el cual s\[IAcute] tiene sentido en este caso. Los otros puntos de \
equilibrio obedecen la ecuaci\[OAcute]n algebraica \n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["N", "TI"], "*2"], "-", 
         StyleBox["P", "TI"], 
         SuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["N", "TI"], "*"], "+", 
         FractionBox[
          RowBox[{"\[Mu]", 
            StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
            StyleBox["P", "TI"]}], "\[Alpha]"], "\[LongEqual]", "0"}], 
       TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "N^{*2}-PN^*+\\frac{\\mu AP}{\\alpha}=0", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c8a3dd27-e0fe-7844-85a4-5ac5f774c609"],
 "\nlo cual resulta en dos puntos de equilibrio\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SubsuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["N", "TI"], 
          RowBox[{"2", ",", "3"}], "*"], "\[LongEqual]", 
         FractionBox[
          RowBox[{
            StyleBox["P", "TI"], "\[PlusMinus]", 
            SqrtBox[
             RowBox[{
               SuperscriptBox[
                StyleBox["P", "TI"], "2"], "-", "4", 
               FractionBox[
                RowBox[{"\[Mu]", 
                  StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
                  StyleBox["P", "TI"]}], "\[Alpha]"]}]]}], "2"]}], 
       TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "N_{2,3}^*=\\frac{P\\pm\\sqrt{P^2-4\\frac{\\mu AP}{\\alpha}}}{2}", 
     "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cfd385c5-9b6c-8448-a389-0c76a91da7aa"],
 "\nDe nuevo, el punto de bifurcaci\[OAcute]n se da cuando los dos se \
fusionan y tienen el valor ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       FractionBox[
        StyleBox["P", "TI"], "2"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "\\frac{P}{2}", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4e59abd0-6fb9-0e4a-a7bc-e4f4d9f65f2f"],
 ". Esto pasa cuando ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["P", "TI"], "2"], "-", "4", 
         FractionBox[
          RowBox[{"\[Mu]", 
            StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
            StyleBox["P", "TI"]}], "\[Alpha]"], "\[LongEqual]", "0"}], 
       TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "P^2-4\\frac{\\mu AP}{\\alpha}=0", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a24ed243-faf0-ae42-bc98-62fba7c3eb32"],
 ", es decir, en el valor cr\[IAcute]tico de ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       StyleBox["A", "TI"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "A", 
     "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fb22d6c7-6efc-8542-a881-2e78a43853d9"],
 "\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         StyleBox["A", "TI"], "\[LongEqual]", 
         FractionBox[
          RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", 
            StyleBox["P", "TI"]}], 
          RowBox[{"4", "\[Mu]"}]]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, 
     "input" -> "A=\\frac{\\alpha P}{4\\mu}", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "43e9b57f-c025-684d-bb32-36f3f11f7e98"],
 ". Por lo tanto, \[EAcute]ste es el criterio para que el movimiento pueda \
sobrevivir si el n\[UAcute]mero de personas no es suficiente para alcanzar la \
probabilidad de convencimiento m\[AAcute]xima. Para calcular su estabilidad, \
podemos aplicar un criterio similar al del caso anterior. Calculamos la \
estabilidad del cero usando la derivada,\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["f", "TI"], "\[Prime]"], 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           StyleBox["N", "TI"], ")"}], "\[LongEqual]", 
         FractionBox[
          RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", 
            StyleBox["N", "TI"]}], 
          RowBox[{
            StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
            StyleBox["P", "TI"]}]], 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           RowBox[{"2", 
             StyleBox["P", "TI"], "-", "3", 
             StyleBox["N", "TI"]}], ")"}], "-", "\[Mu]"}], TraditionalForm], 
     "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "f'(N)=\\frac{\\alpha N}{AP}(2P-3N)-\\mu", 
     "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "13821345-d41d-374e-8119-8565d81df0b1"],
 "\nEvaluando en cero, vemos que al igual que la foma anterior,\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["f", "TI"], "\[Prime]"], 
         RowBox[{"(", "0", ")"}], "\[LongEqual]", "-", "\[Mu]"}], 
       TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "f'(0)=-\\mu", "state" -> 
     "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e5cd9a5a-7e6d-b240-8e2e-711de49be956"],
 ",\npor lo que ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SubsuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["N", "TI"], "1", "*"], "\[LongEqual]", "0"}], 
       TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "N_1^*=0", "state" -> 
     "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a479008b-3c2b-3345-a8f8-32913729cb7e"],
 " siempre es estable, y por lo tanto ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SubsuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["N", "TI"], "2", "*"], "\[LongEqual]", 
         FractionBox[
          RowBox[{
            StyleBox["P", "TI"], "-", 
            SqrtBox[
             RowBox[{
               SuperscriptBox[
                StyleBox["P", "TI"], "2"], "-", "4", 
               FractionBox[
                RowBox[{"\[Mu]", 
                  StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
                  StyleBox["P", "TI"]}], "\[Alpha]"]}]]}], "2"]}], 
       TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "N_{2}^*=\\frac{P-\\sqrt{P^2-4\\frac{\\mu AP}{\\alpha}}}{2}", "state" -> 
     "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "131af1fd-543a-954c-b102-3aaf374bf7bc"],
 " es inestable y ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SubsuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["N", "TI"], "3", "*"], "\[LongEqual]", 
         FractionBox[
          RowBox[{
            StyleBox["P", "TI"], "+", 
            SqrtBox[
             RowBox[{
               SuperscriptBox[
                StyleBox["P", "TI"], "2"], "-", "4", 
               FractionBox[
                RowBox[{"\[Mu]", 
                  StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
                  StyleBox["P", "TI"]}], "\[Alpha]"]}]]}], "2"]}], 
       TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "N_{3}^*=\\frac{P+\\sqrt{P^2-4\\frac{\\mu AP}{\\alpha}}}{2}", "state" -> 
     "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bd7d6066-6c13-1e44-87cb-c468a83cbad1"],
 " es estable. Dado que en este caso ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["f", "TI"], "\[Prime]"], "(", 
         StyleBox["N", "TI"], ")"}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, 
     "input" -> "f'(N)", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "24da5aa6-4ccb-d24e-8178-c74343645b38"],
 " no es complicado, podemos corroborar estas conclusiones evaluando los dos \
puntos de equilibrio, obteniendo\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["f", "TI"], "\[Prime]"], 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           SubsuperscriptBox[
            StyleBox["N", "TI"], 
            RowBox[{"2", ",", "3"}], "*"], ")"}], "\[LongEqual]", 
         FractionBox[
          RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", 
            SuperscriptBox[
             StyleBox["N", "TI"], "*"]}], 
          RowBox[{
            StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
            StyleBox["P", "TI"]}]], 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           RowBox[{
             StyleBox["P", "TI"], "-", "2", 
             SuperscriptBox[
              StyleBox["N", "TI"], "*"]}], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm], 
     "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "f'(N_{2,3}^*)=\\frac{\\alpha N^*}{AP}(P-2N^*})", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2631e8d6-33d9-da4f-983b-727ddd968115"],
 "\ndonde se us\[OAcute] la ecuaci\[OAcute]n ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         StyleBox["f", "TI"], 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           SubsuperscriptBox[
            StyleBox["N", "TI"], 
            RowBox[{"2", ",", "3"}], "*"], ")"}], "\[LongEqual]", "0"}], 
       TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "f(N_{2,3}^*)=0", "state" -> 
     "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "50debfdb-e8a4-e74d-b536-abe1753cbd97"],
 " que cumplen los puntos de equilibrio (\[DownQuestion]puedes ver \
c\[OAcute]mo?) para simplificar la expresi\[OAcute]n. Como todos los par\
\[AAcute]metros, as\[IAcute] como el n\[UAcute]mero de personas, son n\
\[UAcute]meros positivos, la estabilidad de los puntos de equilibrio depende \
de ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         StyleBox["P", "TI"], "-", "2", 
         SuperscriptBox[
          StyleBox["N", "TI"], "*"]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, 
     "input" -> "P-2N^*", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d70c29f5-ace3-ef47-83d4-65fb0e964e3a"],
 ". Una sencilla sustituci\[OAcute]n muestra que ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       SubsuperscriptBox[
        StyleBox["N", "TI"], "2", "*"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, 
     "input" -> "N_2^*", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7f497d55-68b6-fa4c-8533-f93f7e6dd562"],
 " es inestable y ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       SubsuperscriptBox[
        StyleBox["N", "TI"], "3", "*"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, 
     "input" -> "N_3^*", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "07eb5015-7c5d-6a43-b9f8-e41ef54242e6"],
 " es positiva. "
}], "Text",
